<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 568/76 of 15 March 1976 amending Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 568/76, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 veise- ja vasikalihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta 15. m&auml;rts 1976 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1855/74 (3), lays down intervention arrangements including the compulsory buying-in of beef and veal meeting certain quality requirements; whereas, in the light of recent experience, it seems appropriate to provide for the possibility of suspending the intervention measures in regions where prices are relatively high, in order to avoid production for intervention purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 (veise- ja vasikalihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (2) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1855/74 (3)) s&auml;testatakse sekkumiskord, mis sisaldab teatavatele kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele vastava veise- ja vasikaliha kohustuslikku kokkuostmist; viimaseid kogemusi silmas pidades tundub olevat asjakohane n&auml;ha ette v&otilde;imalus peatada sekkumismeetmete kohaldamine piirkondades, kus hinnad on suhteliselt k&otilde;rged, selleks et v&auml;ltida tootmist sekkumise jaoks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 18 of Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 provides for the possibility of granting of an export refund; whereas experience has shown that the measures taken do not always give the trade the certainty as regards amounts and periods of validity of the refunds that it requires; whereas provision should therefore be made to allow refunds to be fixed in advance, </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 artikliga 18 n&auml;hakse ette v&otilde;imalus anda eksporditoetust; kogemused on n&auml;idanud, et v&otilde;etud meetmed ei anna kaubanduse puhul alati vajalikku kindlust toetuse suuruse ja kehtivusaja osas; seep&auml;rast tuleks s&auml;testada v&otilde;imalus kinnitada toetused eelnevalt, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following paragraph shall be inserted in Article 6 of Regulation (EEC) No 805/68: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 artiklisse 6 lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ige: </eesti>
<inglise> "3a. </inglise>
<eesti> "3a. </eesti>
<inglise> However, if during the 1976/1977 marketing year the price recorded in accordance with the preceding paragraphs on the representative markets of a Member State or of a region within a Member State is equal to or more than 95 % of the guide price during a given period, the intervention measures referred to in paragraphs 1 and 3 may be partially or totally suspended in the Member State or region concerned. " </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigi v&otilde;i liikmesriigi piirkonna t&uuml;&uuml;pilistel turgudel eelmiste l&otilde;igete kohaselt 1976/1977. majandusaasta jooksul registreeritud hind moodustab teatava ajavahemiku soovitushinnast v&auml;hemalt 95%, v&otilde;ib l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 3 nimetatud sekkumismeetmete kohaldamise asjaomases liikmesriigis v&otilde;i piirkonnas siiski osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult peatada." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 18 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 artikli 18 l&otilde;ige 4 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "4. </inglise>
<eesti> "4. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission in accordance with the voting procedure laid down in Article 43 (2) of the Treaty, shall adopt general rules for the granting and advance fixing of export refunds and lay down criteria for fixing the amount of such refunds. " </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;tab komisjoni ettepanekul asutamislepingu artikli 43 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud h&auml;&auml;letamise korras vastu eksporditoetuste andmise ja eelneva kinnitamise &uuml;ldeeskirjad ning eksporditoetuste suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramise kriteeriumid." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 15 March 1976. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 15. m&auml;rtsil 1976. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 15 March 1976. </inglise>
